pull_request.title: added user activity badges
pull_request.body: **3 Badges added :** 1. rookie: user activity points 5 2. vibin : user activity points 20 3. legend : user activity points 30 - All badges are stored under static/badges folder in server. - User collections in mongoDB stores badges as urls from static . Eg: static/rookie.png. **Badge activity definition :** - Every badge and its threshold with its url is defined in badgesConfig.js **addition of new endpoint user/activity :** - New endpoint to handle user activity status is included under routes folder as "user-activity-check" . - Accordingly, use effect components are added in places.tsx and findfriends.tsx **auth (login/signup) calls :** - In auth.tsx, login is routed to /entry-point/login and signup to /entry-point/signup to use mongoDB This is how the badges and user data appears for user profile from database:

commits.message:
Add tech stack proposal and one-click start script

Introduces a comprehensive tech stack and architecture proposal for STL Manager, outlining phase-by-phase implementation, technology choices, and rationale. Adds a Windows batch script for one-click local startup, including virtual environment setup and API/UI launch.

Update UpdateCustomLocation to accept nullable DateTime

This change modifies the `UpdateCustomLocation` method in both `CustomLocationDataRepository.cs` and `ICustomLocationDataRepository.cs` to accept a nullable `DateTime?` parameter instead of a non-nullable `DateTime`. This allows the method to handle cases where the `now` parameter may be null.

Refactor MapPinTag and CustomLocationPin classes

Updated CustomLocationPin to use SetCustomLocationTag for Tag property.
Enhanced MapPinTag with new properties: ArrivalLocationId, CustomLocationKey, and BoardName.
Introduced IsCustomLocation and IsArrivalLocation properties.
Changed constructors to private for better encapsulation and added static methods for instance creation.

Update ArrivalLocationPin to include ID parameter

Modified ArrivalLocationPin class to add an ID parameter in its constructors and updated the Initialize method accordingly. Adjusted the GetArrivalLocationPin method in ArrivalLocationDataRepository to utilize the new constructor. Updated LocationPageViewModel to create ArrivalLocationPin instances with the ID from arrivalLocationData.

Add confirmation prompts for delete and reset actions

Introduce localized strings `ConfirmDelete` and `ConfirmReset` for user confirmation in English and Japanese. Implement event handlers in `LocationPageViewModel` to display confirmation dialogs when deleting an arrival location or resetting a custom location, enhancing user interaction and experience.

Enhance pin classes and update location management logic

- Added `Id` property to `ArrivalLocationPin` for easier access to `ArrivalLocationId`.
- Introduced `SetIcon` method in `ArrivalLocationPin` for icon management.
- Modified `CustomLocationPin` to use a static `SetIcon` method and added properties/methods for visit status management.
- Refined `OnInfoWindowLongClicked` in `LocationPageViewModel` to improve deletion and update logic for both pin types, including confirmation dialogs and database interactions.

pull_request.title: Bump actions/download-artifact from 4 to 5
pull_request.body:
Bumps [actions/download-artifact](https://github.com/actions/download-artifact) from 4 to 5.
Release notes

Sourced from actions/download-artifact's releases.

v5.0.0

What's Changed

  • Update README.md by @​nebuk89 in actions/download-artifact#407
  • BREAKING fix: inconsistent path behavior for single artifact downloads by ID by @​GrantBirki in actions/download-artifact#416

v5.0.0

🚨 Breaking Change

This release fixes an inconsistency in path behavior for single artifact downloads by ID. If you're downloading single artifacts by ID, the output path may change.

What Changed

Previously, single artifact downloads behaved differently depending on how you specified the artifact:

  • By name: name: my-artifact → extracted to path/ (direct)
  • By ID: artifact-ids: 12345 → extracted to path/my-artifact/ (nested)

Now both methods are consistent:

  • By name: name: my-artifact → extracted to path/ (unchanged)
  • By ID: artifact-ids: 12345 → extracted to path/ (fixed - now direct)

Migration Guide

✅ No Action Needed If:
  • You download artifacts by name
  • You download multiple artifacts by ID
  • You already use merge-multiple: true as a workaround
⚠️ Action Required If:

You download single artifacts by ID and your workflows expect the nested directory structure.

Before v5 (nested structure):

- uses: actions/download-artifact@v4
  with:
    artifact-ids: 12345
    path: dist
# Files were in: dist/my-artifact/

Where my-artifact is the name of the artifact you previously uploaded

To maintain old behavior (if needed):

issue.title: Add more files and directories for "make dist"
issue.body:
This PR adds existing files and directories to the archive created with `make dist` and `make distcheck` and removes some that weren't used.
It also builds more existing tests, but it doesn't execute them during `make check` because they would fail or are too simple:
* `example` (is an example)
* `func_chk` (checks Hamlib sources)
* `sendraw` (needs a rig or a simulator)
* `simple` (is an example)
* `testnet` (has hardcoded addresses that won't resolve)
* `testsecurity` (this could be run and could be added in another PR)

comment.body:
In my opinion, a distribution tarball is for developers and users that do not use git.
It is true that github provides a way to download a snapshot of the repository, but it doesn't check if it actually builds.
